{
  "type": "PrimaryTheme",
  "number": 5700,
  "title": "headship",
  "comment": "The quality of being in a position of leadership or guidance. Headship has to do with God's relation to this created world, and to his ordering of relationships within it. Headship among human beings does not necessarily signify superior status, but rather a role of leadership and care. Scripture sees it as involving servanthood, and views Jesus Christ as the supreme model of this.",
  "refgroup": null,
